  "text": "Across the NumPy and SciPy repositories, a total of 9 Python source files (.py) contain references to the deprecated numpy.distutils module. These references take three forms: direct imports, vendored code marked with comments, and mentions in docstrings and help text.\n\nIn the NumPy repository (sg-evals/numpy v2.2.2), 8 files reference numpy.distutils:\n\n1. numpy/__init__.py - Contains a dynamic import of numpy.distutils at line 383, within a __getattr__ function that handles attribute access fallback. This import checks if distutils is available in __numpy_submodules__ and raises an AttributeError for Python 3.12+ where numpy.distutils is no longer available.\n\n2. numpy/_build_utils/process_src_template.py - References numpy.distutils in a comment at line 8 ('Convoluted because we can't import from numpy.distutils') explaining why the code avoids importing from numpy.distutils during the NumPy build process.\n\n3. numpy/compat/py3k.py - References numpy.distutils.misc_util.exec_mod_from_location in the docstring of the npy_load_module function at line 120, noting it as an alternative implementation.\n\n4. numpy/f2py/__init__.py - References numpy.distutils in a docstring at line 32, noting that the get_include() function is 'not needed when building an extension with `numpy.distutils` directly from `.f` and/or `.pyf` files'.\n\n5. numpy/f2py/f2py2e.py - Contains two imports from numpy.distutils: at line 669 imports numpy.distutils.fcompiler to handle --fcompiler command-line options, and at line 776 imports numpy.distutils.system_info.show_all for the --help-link option.\n\n6. numpy/f2py/_src_pyf.py - Contains vendored code from numpy.distutils.from_template, marked by comments at lines 4-5 ('START OF CODE VENDORED FROM `numpy.distutils.from_template`') and 239-240 ('END OF CODE VENDORED FROM `numpy.distutils.from_template`').\n\n7. numpy/f2py/diagnose.py - Imports numpy.distutils at line 45 (with fallback to numpy_distutils) and imports numpy.distutils.cpuinfo at line 127 for diagnostic purposes.\n\n8. numpy/f2py/_backends/_distutils.py - Imports multiple components from numpy.distutils at lines 3-5: from numpy.distutils.core import setup and Extension, from numpy.distutils.system_info import get_info, and from numpy.distutils.misc_util import dict_append.\n\nIn the SciPy repository (sg-evals/scipy v1.15.1), 1 file references numpy.distutils:\n\n1. tools/generate_f2pymod.py - Contains vendored code from numpy.distutils.from_template, marked by comments at lines 14-15 ('START OF CODE VENDORED FROM `numpy.distutils.from_template`') and 256-257 ('END OF CODE VENDORED FROM `numpy.distutils.from_template`'). This is a tool for processing f2py template files.\n\nThese residual references reflect that while the distutils module itself has been removed from NumPy 2.0+, consuming code (particularly in the f2py build system) and vendored template processing code still maintain dependencies on the deprecated numpy.distutils API. The references to numpy.distutils in scikit-learn and pandas reveal zero residual references, confirming these libraries have completed their migration away from numpy.distutils."
